job.job_description: Dominion Energy is committed to providing reliable, affordable, and increasingly clean energy that powers our customers every day. If you want to work for a purpose-driven company that values safety and collaboration, we’re looking for you. You won’t just find a job here; you’ll find your career. Review the position below and apply today. We offer a hybrid 3-2 work schedule (three days in the office, two days of teleworking) to accommodate the need for flexibility. Military service members and veterans with ranks from E3-E5, W1-W2, or O1-O3, plus appropriate equivalent combination of education and years of experience as outlined below will be considered for this opportunity. Job Summary We Strive to Drive Power Innovation Through Data The nature of the grid is in flux. We on the Strategic Initiatives - Operations Analytics team see this challenge and aim to rise to the occasion. Our team mandate is to bridge the gap between real-world system data and provide consumable business intelligence to help steer the future of how we monitor and manage the grid. Our fast-growing team is responsible for the capture, curation, utilization, and application of time-series data, including SCADA and Synchrophasors. Our work is to steward this data and ensure its analysis and outputs provide our business and the industry with the ability to adapt and meet the demands of a shifting energy landscape. We seek the curious and creative, the self-motivated, and those driven by the pursuit of driving change. We Seek Joint Expertise in Power Systems & Data Storytelling Our team is seeking an engineer with a background in power systems and data engineering technology and development to help further our business’ power system analytic capabilities. An ideal candidate is driven by the pursuit of excellence – this is not a job for wrench-turning, but rather for those compelled to identify problems and solve them with critical thinking abilities and working with a multi-faceted team. Candidates must bring the ability to identify gaps in knowledge and organizational capability and pinpoint uses for data and storytelling techniques to ensure we serve the business with improved data-decision making technology. A successful candidate will focus on: Forging new relationships across the organization in search of applicable use cases and opportunities to use time series data as a backbone for analysis and decision-making and guiding/building out solutions. Ongoing account management – working with existing partners to meet established project requirements and ensure any analytic/application outputs meet the stated objective of customer established requirements. Ensuring uptime and proper operation of our PI system resources to ensure current and future state operations of PI are nominally operational for the organization. Continuous learning: whether it’s new technologies or growth in our company’s vertical, our most successful team members are those who have an intrinsic desire to learn and improve. Exploring new techniques and PI features to model time-series and asset data. Whether leveraging native PI capabilities, or utilizing SDK and API capabilities to establish data services and create improved capabilities outside. Must be able to meet NERC qualifications. Relocation assistance may be offered to the successful candidate. Sponsorship assistance may be offered to the successful candidate. Military service members and veterans with ranks from E5-E9, W1-CW5, or O3-O6, plus appropriate equivalent combination of education and years of experience as outlined. Required Knowledge, Skills, Abilities & Experience The knowledge, skills, abilities and experiences required for entry into this job include the following: Associate Engineer: 0-2+ years of engineering experience Engineer: 2-5 years of engineering experience Senior Engineer: 5+ years of engineering experience Basic knowledge of engineering concepts, fundamentals and theory. Ability to apply these theories and concepts to complex problems. Preference for knowledge of basic electric power concepts, including electric transmission and distribution, power flow, distributed generation and line protection. Effective decision-making, organization, and problem-solving skills. Ability to communicate effectively, build relationships, and operate independently while aligning to the joint mission of our team. Data Analysis: Interrogating data and carefully posing the right questions to produce insightful and high impact outputs. Candidates should possess strong analytic skills and have a history of using programmatic languages to create data analyses and visualizations that answer specific and properly posed questions. A strong candidate will demonstrate a high degree of proficiency in developing tools including but not limited to Python, C#, PowerBI, Advanced Excel, SQL, and/or ArcGIS. PI Data Engineering (preferred but not required): Much of our PI technology is operated and maintained by our Information Technology team; it is our responsibility to ensure the proper guidance of business requirements to deliver the right core capabilities to the business. Having an understanding of PI technology features (specifically OSISoft and/or AVEVA) would be beneficial for this role. This includes PI Data Archive, PI Asset Framework, PI Vision, PI Business Analytics Integrator, PI Web API, PI AF SDK, and common functionalities across those platforms. Power Systems Fundamentals (preferred but not required): We deal with transmission systems data. A candidate with power systems acumen will have a more streamlined entry to posing the right engineering questions and devising highly applicable analytic results – while this is not required, we will look for candidates with a demonstrated history in professional training and development. The candidate should demonstrate excellent professional ethics. REQUIRED ENGINEERING CRITERIA: For placement of a candidate in the Engineer job series, the following criteria must be met: Possess a 4-year Engineering degree from an ABET accredited Engineering program based on the year that the Engineering program was accredited by ABET, or Possess a 4-year Engineering degree from an institution outside of the U.S. which is accredited through the country's own Engineering accrediting body under the Washington Accord as a full signatory, and is a degree that was recognized by the country's accrediting body on or after the date that full signatory status was achieved, or Possess a 4-year degree in Engineering (non-ABET accredited), Physics, Chemistry, Math or Engineering Technology and a post-graduate Engineering degree from an institution where the undergraduate degree in the same Engineering discipline is ABET-accredited based on the year the Engineering program was accredited by ABET, or Holds or has previously held a valid U.S. Professional Engineer license.
